            <div class="row text-row">
                <div class="col-lg-10 offset-lg-1 no-padding ">
                    <div class="plash-breast">
                        <div class="breast-title">What is a Breast Augmentation</div>
                        <div class="breast-text">
                            Breast augmentation is a surgical procedure that involves placing a saline or silicone
                            implant to enhance breast size. Although breast augmentation is one of the most commonly
                            performed procedures in the United States and Houston, Texas, the procedure should be very
                            individualized for each patient. Decisions regarding the type of implant (saline or
                            silicone), size of implant, structure of implant (the surface of the implant and the shape
                            of the implant), breast incision used, placement of the breast implant, and creation of the
                            breast pocket for the implant are all key decisions that a patient makes along with our
                            plastic surgeons to create their ideal look.

                            <p>It is important to note that while breast augmentation can enhance the size and shape of
                                your breast, it cannot significantly lift your breast or relieve breast pain. If you
                                have significant sagging of your breast due to age, pregnancy, nursing, or weight loss,
                                you may require a breast lift with or without breast augmentation to achieve your
                                desired look.</p>
                        </div>
