    <section class="text-section pb-240" id="section-why-breast-aug">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <h2 class="wow fadeInUp center text-center">Why do you want breast augmentation in Houston, Texas?</h2>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div data-jarallax-element="-150" class="text-section-box"></div>
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row text-row">
                <div class="col-lg-6">
                    <div class="text-section-block">
                        <h3>Size</h3>
                        <p>
                            Most women in Houston, Texas choose to have breast augmentation to increase breast size.
                            Whether
                            you want to fill out clothing better, look better in dresses, tops, or swim suits, or feel
                            more
                            confident unclothed, breast augmentation can help you achieve the figure you want.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Breast implants are typically measured in cubic centimeters or cc’s. In general, 100-200
                            cc’s will enhance your breast by approximately one cup size. However, not all bra cup sizes
                            are created equal. A bra size at Victoria Secret may be different than a bra size found at
                            Nordstrom, Target, or other department stores. When determining breast implant size during
                            breast augmentation consultation, you should give your TOPS plastic surgeon an idea of the
                            before and after look you are trying to achieve, so they can help guide you to find the best
                            breast augmentation size for you.
                        </p>
                        <p>During your consultation, plastic surgeons and staff at The Oaks Plastic Surgery work with
                            you to choose a breast implant size that achieves your breast enhancement goals and best
                            fits your anatomy. Our Houston plastic surgeons encourage you to bring swim suit tops, nice
                            dresses or tops, and T-shirts to try on different breast implant sizes during your
                            consultation to find the best size for you. </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="text-section-block">
                        <h3>Asymmetry</h3>
                        <p>
                            If your breasts are asymmetric, you are not alone. Most patients have some form of breast
                            asymmetry. If you find that your breast asymmetry causes you to constantly need to pad your
                            bra, feel self conscious in dresses or bathing suits, or makes it difficult to fit in
                            clothes, breast augmentation can help.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="text-section-block">
                        <h3>After Weight Loss </h3>
                        <p>
                            The Oaks Plastic Surgery is a huge advocate of healthy lifestyles in Houston, Texas and are
                            incredibly proud of our patients who achieve and sustain significant weight loss.
                            Unfortunately, one area that women often don’t want to lose, but tend to lose first is in
                            the breast area. Weight loss can lead to smaller, deflated breasts. Breast augmentation can
                            help improve the shape and size of your breasts for a more aesthetic appearance that is in
                            proportion to your new body.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            It is important to note that after significant weight loss, it is very common to experience
                            more significant breast sagging, which you make you a better candidate for a breast lift
                            (mastopexy) with or without breast augmentation. Your TOPS plastic surgeon will personally
                            discuss these options with you and provide a breast procedure that will fit your specific
                            goals.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-6 pt-lg-5">
                    <div class="text-section-block">
                        <h3>After Pregnancy</h3>
                        <p class="align-content-end">
                            Breast augmentation is a common part of a Mommy Makeover. Many women who have had children,
                            especially those who nursed, experience significant deflation of their breast tissue. This
                            can lead healthy, beautiful, and active women to feel embarrassed and self-conscious in
                            clothing or with their partners. Breast augmentation can help restore the volume lost after
                            pregnancy or breastfeeding and help give a subtle lift to the breast.
                        </p>
                        <p>It is important to note that if your breasts experienced more significant sagging after
                            pregnancy, which is very common, you may be a better candidate for a breast lift (mastopexy)
                            with or without breast augmentation. Our TOPS plastic surgeons will personally discuss these
                            options with you and provide a procedure that will fit your specific goals. </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="text-section-block">
                        <h3>Breast Shape</h3>
                        <p class="align-content-end">
                            Some patients suffer from a condition called tuberous breast syndrome, in which patients
                            have a very narrowed, small, sagging breasts that appear misshapen. The TOPS plastic
                            surgeons are specifically trained to deal with these types of breasts in a different manner
                            to fully treat the malformed breast(s) and create a rounder, fuller, more feminine
                            appearance with a specialized breast augmentation and lift procedure.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="text-section-block">
                        <h3>Post Breast Cancer</h3>
                        <p class="align-content-end">
                            If you have undergone mastectomy or lumpectomy for breast cancer, you may have breast
                            asymmetry or malformation that causes your clothes or bras to fit uncomfortably, makes you
                            self-conscious, or reminds you of the trauma of breast cancer. If you have undergone surgery
                            for breast cancer or have recently been diagnosed with breast cancer or are planning to
                            undergo surgery, our TOPS plastic surgeons are committed to helping you through this
                            difficult time in your life and restoring your body to make you whole again. Please visit
                            our <a href="/breast-reconstruction-houston">breast reconstruction</a> page for more
                            information.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    
