                        <h2 class="text-h-mort">
                            What can you expect at your Initial consultation at The Oaks Plastic Surgery in Houston,
                            Texas?
                        </h2>
                        <span>
                                    If you are interested in breast augmentation in Houston, Texas, an appointment can be made with one of our TOPS plastic surgeons: Dr. Danielle Andry or Dr. Nandi Wijay.  You can expect the initial consultation to last an hour or more. In your consultation, your TOPS plastic surgeon will:
                                </span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-6 no-padding service-left-cta">
                    <ul data-jarallax-element="-100">
                        <li>
                            Listen to your specific complaints and goals
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Perform a thorough examination, focusing on your individual anatomy. Careful measurements
                            and photographs will be taken.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            If breast augmentation is the right option for you, your TOPS plastic surgeon will discuss
                            details of the surgical procedures that are offered and which approach is right for you.
                            Details regarding implant options including saline or silicone, textured or smooth implants,
                            round or anatomical implants, implant size, implant position (over the muscle or under the
                            muscle), and incision site (under the breast fold or inframammary fold incision, around the
                            nipple or periareolar incision, or through the axilla or transaxillary incision) will be
                            thoroughly discussed. You will be given an opportunity to feel the different types of
                            implants and try on sizes.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            The risks and benefits of breast augmentation will be
                            thoroughly outlined and particular emphasis will be placed on the the risks and benefits
                            regarding each of the implant types, incisions, and approaches.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            You will be given ample opportunity to ask questions from both our TOPS
                            plastic surgeons and cosmetic surgery staff regarding breast augmentation surgery
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            You will be sent home with a packet of information regarding the breast augmentation
                            including a detailed consent form and instructions for before and after your breast
                            augmentation in Houston, Texas.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
