            <div class="row text-row">
                <div class="col-lg-6 " id="section-day-of-expect">
                    <div class="text-section-block">
                        <h3>What can you expect on the day of your breast augmentation in Houston, Texas?</h3>
                        <p>
                            The day of your breast augmentation surgery, your TOPS plastic surgeon will meet you in the
                            preoperative area to go over any last minute questions or concerns you may have. Your
                            plastic surgeon may make some preoperative markings and will perform extensive checks and
                            attention to detail ensuring high quality care and safety. You will meet the
                            anesthesiologist and their team, as well as the members of our plastic surgery operative
                            team.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            During the procedure, our plastic surgeons pay meticulous attention to detail and work as a
                            team to ensure a great result with a focus on safety and quality. Your plastic surgeon will
                            sit you upright immediately after implants are placed to ensure you have the best result and
                            will continue to adjust the placement of the implants until they are fully satisfied with
                            your cosmetic result. Your family will be updated of your status periodically and will be
                            able to talk with the plastic surgeon one-on-one after the procedure is completed. Breast
                            Augmentation procedure typically takes the TOPS plastic surgeons between 1-2 hours.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-6 " id="section-recovery-expect">
                    <div class="text-section-block">
                        <h3>What can you expect for recovery after a Breast Augmentation at The Oaks Plastic Surgery in
                            Houston, Texas?</h3>
                        <p class="align-content-end">
                            After your breast augmentation, you will be placed in a surgical wrap or surgical bra. You
                            will have a light dressing covering the incision. Mild swelling is typical after surgery.
                            You may shower 24 hrs after the procedure. The TOPS plastic surgeons employ a multimodal
                            pain regimen to decrease or eliminate your need for narcotic pain medication, which allows
                            are patients to recover quickly and feel more like themselves soon after surgery. Most of
                            our patients are ready to go back to work within a week. Our plastic surgeons and cosmetic
                            surgery staff in Houston will see you or communicate with you daily to ensure proper
                            healing. Most of the swelling begins to subside over the first week or two and typically
                            resolves by 4-6 weeks. We advise that you refrain from strenuous activity or heavy lifting
                            greater than 10 lbs for 4-6 weeks during the healing process. </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

